{"type":"message","id":"4cf60ed3","parentId":"274c717e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:54:41.463Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_kbujx49i43h4_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- CFI � 0.5\r\n- freq � 3  \r\n- freq < 120\r\n\r\nThis means tokens with freq=160 are explicitly excluded by the freq < 120 condition.\r\n\r\nThe pending experiment wants to test:\r\n- score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nBut this formula doesn't capture the freq < 120 constraint. The next step should be to design and run this experiment.\r\n\r\nSince this is a pulse for a stateless agent, I need to take ONE concrete action. The most logical next step is to:\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll document the proposed scoring function modification in the research file. I'll record the experimental design, noting the need to add an upper frequency constraint to prevent constant format token inflation. This creates a clear path for testing the hybrid CFIxFreq scoring approach, addressing the limitation in the current formula.\r\n\r\nThe key modification involves capping the frequency contribution at 120, ensuring that high-frequency constant tokens don't dominate the scoring. This approach aligns with the three-dimensional compression filter requirement, adding a critical boundary condition to the scoring mechanism.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression experiment established that three-dimensional filtering (CFI � 0.5 AND freq � 3 AND freq < 120) is needed, but the pending hybrid scoring formula `score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)` as stated doesn't penalize constant-format tokens (freq=160). The next step is designing and documenting the experiment protocol.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate an experiment protocol document for the Hybrid CFIxFreq scoring test, incorporating the freq < 120 upper bound constraint learned from the CFI experiment.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Hybrid CFIxFreq Scoring Experiment Protocol\r\n**Status:** DESIGNED  \r\n**Date:** 2026-03-24\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nFrom CFI Compression Synthesis:\r\n- CFI � 0.7 AND freq < 60 = TOO aggressive (92.9% recall loss)\r\n- Constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1.0) are NOT causal despite high scores\r\n- Need to distinguish \"metaprogramming artifacts\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n\r\n## Scoring Function (Corrected)\r\n\r\n**Version A (Threshold):** CFI � 0.5 AND freq ? [3, 120)  \r\n**Version B (Hybrid):** score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)  \r\n\r\n**Key insight:** Version B as stated still scores constant-format at 1.0.  \r\n**Correction:** Apply freq < 120 as a hard boundary, then scale:\r\n\r\n```\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120) x [freq(T) < 120]\r\n         = 0 if freq � 120\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n| Metric | Version A (Threshold) | Version B (Hybrid) |\r\n|--------|----------------------|-------------------|\r\n| Precision@100 | baseline | target: � 0.5653 |\r\n| Recall@200 | baseline | target: recover lost recall |\r\n| F1 | compute | compute |\r\n\r\n**Split:** 200 pulses, 80/20 (train/test)\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nHybrid scoring will:\r\n1. Penalize constant-format tokens (freq=160) to ~0 score\r\n2. Preserve high-CFI research tokens (freq<120) \r\n3. Achieve F1 > threshold-only approach\r\n\r\n## Run Command\r\n```bash\r\npython3 scripts/cfi_hybrid_experiment.py --pulses 200 --split 0.8\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcome\r\nIf BOTH versions fail to distinguish constant-format from research trajectory, we need a FOURTH dimension (e.g., token length, position, or structural pattern).\r\nfile: research/HYBRID_CFI_FREQ_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:54:35"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":625,"aggregated":"- CFI � 0.5\r\n- freq � 3  \r\n- freq < 120\r\n\r\nThis means tokens with freq=160 are explicitly excluded by the freq < 120 condition.\r\n\r\nThe pending experiment wants to test:\r\n- score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nBut this formula doesn't capture the freq < 120 constraint. The next step should be to design and run this experiment.\r\n\r\nSince this is a pulse for a stateless agent, I need to take ONE concrete action. The most logical next step is to:\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll document the proposed scoring function modification in the research file. I'll record the experimental design, noting the need to add an upper frequency constraint to prevent constant format token inflation. This creates a clear path for testing the hybrid CFIxFreq scoring approach, addressing the limitation in the current formula.\r\n\r\nThe key modification involves capping the frequency contribution at 120, ensuring that high-frequency constant tokens don't dominate the scoring. This approach aligns with the three-dimensional compression filter requirement, adding a critical boundary condition to the scoring mechanism.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression experiment established that three-dimensional filtering (CFI � 0.5 AND freq � 3 AND freq < 120) is needed, but the pending hybrid scoring formula `score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)` as stated doesn't penalize constant-format tokens (freq=160). The next step is designing and documenting the experiment protocol.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate an experiment protocol document for the Hybrid CFIxFreq scoring test, incorporating the freq < 120 upper bound constraint learned from the CFI experiment.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Hybrid CFIxFreq Scoring Experiment Protocol\r\n**Status:** DESIGNED  \r\n**Date:** 2026-03-24\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nFrom CFI Compression Synthesis:\r\n- CFI � 0.7 AND freq < 60 = TOO aggressive (92.9% recall loss)\r\n- Constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1.0) are NOT causal despite high scores\r\n- Need to distinguish \"metaprogramming artifacts\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n\r\n## Scoring Function (Corrected)\r\n\r\n**Version A (Threshold):** CFI � 0.5 AND freq ? [3, 120)  \r\n**Version B (Hybrid):** score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)  \r\n\r\n**Key insight:** Version B as stated still scores constant-format at 1.0.  \r\n**Correction:** Apply freq < 120 as a hard boundary, then scale:\r\n\r\n```\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120) x [freq(T) < 120]\r\n         = 0 if freq � 120\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n| Metric | Version A (Threshold) | Version B (Hybrid) |\r\n|--------|----------------------|-------------------|\r\n| Precision@100 | baseline | target: � 0.5653 |\r\n| Recall@200 | baseline | target: recover lost recall |\r\n| F1 | compute | compute |\r\n\r\n**Split:** 200 pulses, 80/20 (train/test)\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nHybrid scoring will:\r\n1. Penalize constant-format tokens (freq=160) to ~0 score\r\n2. Preserve high-CFI research tokens (freq<120) \r\n3. Achieve F1 > threshold-only approach\r\n\r\n## Run Command\r\n```bash\r\npython3 scripts/cfi_hybrid_experiment.py --pulses 200 --split 0.8\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcome\r\nIf BOTH versions fail to distinguish constant-format from research trajectory, we need a FOURTH dimension (e.g., token length, position, or structural pattern).\r\nfile: research/HYBRID_CFI_FREQ_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:54:35","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774378481461}}
